President Muhammadu Buhari has expressed sympathy over the accident involving a train and Lagos State BRT staff bus Thursday in Shogunle area of Ikeja. In a reaction to the incident, President Buhari in a statement by presidential spokesman, Garba Shehu said: “The accident at the level crossing involving the train and the BRT staff bus is distressing and extremely sad. I pray for the souls of the deceased and quick recovery of the many who were injured.”  The President commended the Lagos State authorities and Federal Government agencies for promptly getting involved in relief work for the victims.